# Safety net, not the primary mechanism.
#
# wrangler.jsonc points the asset directory at public/, so this file is normally
# unused. It only takes effect if a build ever falls back to treating the
# repository root as the site, which is what happened on the first deploy and
# put .git on the public internet. Keep it.
.git
.gitignore
.assetsignore
wrangler.jsonc
*.md
LICENSE
